rComments: Honestly one of my favourite ever professors. Not only was he helpful when I was confused, but he actually seemed engaged during lectures. As an important side note, he also addressed heteronormativity and straight male privilege during one of the lectures which made me respect him even more.

rComments: Absolutely brilliant. An excellent professor, one of the best theory professors I've had; his musical analyses are great! He stands out in his use of current analytical literature in his courses. He is clear, enthusiastic and helpful, although his courses are hard work, which is naturally expected!

Professor Vande Moortele is a fantastic theory teacher. He really knows his stuff and is very approachable outside of class for extra help. I had no interest in the course before, and still have no interest in music theory, but he made a mandatory credit in a dull subject almost enjoyable.
